  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering generally involves hiding the origins of illegally obtained money through a series of transactions to make it appear legitimate. Specific legal definitions vary by jurisdiction, but typically include:\n\n1. Core elements:\n- Concealing the source of illegal funds\n- Making illegally obtained money appear legal\n- Transferring or disguising criminal proceeds\n\n2. Common legal components:\n- Knowingly processing funds from criminal activity\n- Attempting to legitimize money from unlawful sources\n- Engaging in financial transactions to hide criminal origins\n\n3. Typical criminal activities generating laundered funds:\n- Drug trafficking\n- Fraud\n- Illegal gambling\n- Corruption\n- Terrorist financing\n\n4. Key legal jurisdictions:\n- United States: Bank Secrecy Act\n- European Union: Anti-Money Laundering Directives\n- International: Financial Action Task Force (FATF) standards\n\n5. Typical prosecution requirements:\n- Proving intent\n- Demonstrating knowledge of illegal source\n- Showing deliberate financial manipulation\n\nThe precise definition depends on specific national laws and regulatory frameworks. Legal professionals can provide jurisdiction-specific details.",
